snippet.textDisplay:
So, seeing as how you are building wooden berms now and you also need a little bit more speed for the driveway gap. I was thinking maybe, add a wooden berm landing to the little jump at the end of the snake pit skinny. You know like a reverse shark fin. They did that at dark fest 2020 in South Africa. I’ve always thought that landing needed to be a bit wider anyway and it might help with the speed. That way you can pump and maybe get more boost towards the driveway gap. I don’t know how you would do it. But, That’s my “Seth’s BIke Hacks” thought of the week.

P.S. love the content good sir. Keep it up!

snippet.textDisplay:
While most people are closely watching the development of the coronavirus outbreak in China, it is worth noting that three cases of Black Death were confirmed in Beijing in November 2019.

The “Black Death” news was widely reported by the western media. One example is an NPR article published on November 15, 2019 titled “China Reports 3 Cases Of The Most Dangerous Type Of Plague.” According to the latest updated version of the article, a married couple were both diagnosed with the disease on November 12, and a third case was confirmed on November 16.

As the plague is also a form of contagious bacterial disease that can cause death, one may use preventive measures to protect oneself from the infection.

Around the 14th century, the plague killed nearly one third of the population in Europe, around 50 million people.

Despite the invention of antibiotics and the advancement of modern medicines, the plague has made several comebacks. The most recent outbreak was in Madagascar in 2017, with 2,348 infected and 202 dead.

snippet.textDisplay: Only thing I'd change would be to add a few more planks to the start and have them get progressively larger, almost like an orange quarter. If someone comes in a little too hot, the front wheel is gonna clip the side of the berm and that'll end in a broken rib or collarbone and loose teeth. Eating wooden features is never fun, I've tried.
